         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot &amp; zool Garden, ¶ 25. July 1860 ¶ Reverend &amp; venerable Sir. ¶  ¶ The package of fungi, returned with so valuable notes by you, reached me only 2 weeks after its arrival in Melbourne, bein...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.07.25d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Miles Berkeley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Botany Library, Berkeley correspondence, vol. 9.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Berkeley: </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">1. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">2. Pol. versicolor </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">3. Ag. aspratus [&amp;] Xylaria phosphorea </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">4. Ag. scabriusculus B. (pleurotus) [with 10] </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">5. Lent. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">6. Pez. hirneoloides </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">7. Hern[i] hispidula </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">8. Ag penetrans </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">9. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">10. Lenzites Beckleri, B </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">11. Ag [(lep)] Beckleri, B </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">12. Ster. lobatum </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">13. Cort. Auberianum </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">14. Pol. Xanthopus </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">15. Schiz-commune. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8071in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">(Blank entries against numbers 1 and 9.)</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This list corresponds to the following fungi listed in Berkeley (1873): </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Polyporus (Inodermei) versicolor </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Agaricus (Lepiota) aspratus </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Agaricus ( Pleurotus) scabriusculus </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Lentinus </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Xylaria phosphorea </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Peziza hirneoloides </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Agaricus (Pleurotus) penetrans </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hirneola hispidula </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Lenzites beckleri </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Agaricus (Lepiota) beckleri </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Stereum lobatum </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Corticum auberianum </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Polyporus xanthopus </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Schizophyllum commune.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot &amp; zool Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25. July 1860</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Reverend &amp; venerable Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The package of fungi, returned with so valuable notes by you, reached me only 2 weeks after its arrival in Melbourne, being evidently mislaid at the book-office. Hence it arose, that I could not already express to you by the last mail my deep sense of gratitude &amp; my profound acknowledgement of your generosity of having coupled my humble name with yours, on which so long the brightest lustre of fame shed its rays.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No species jointly named by Berkeley and M validly published <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by 1860 has been found in the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fungi name index</seg>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>(accessed 2 October 2020). However, in B61.02.01, p. 18, M lists <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Agaricus sonderi</seg> as a species jointly published with Berkeley. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">A. muelleri</seg> is also listed there, each as a name only. These species, presumably included as herbarium names with the specimens, were not published until Berkeley (1873), as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">A. sonderianus </seg>and, presumably although there is no synonym stated, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Paxillus muelleri <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="">said to have been collected by M at Wilson's Promontary </seg>(both p. 159), and M was not then included as one of the authors.</p>
               </note> I was in no way entitled to the unexpected honor of becoming a mycologist, altho' I have lately after absolving the investigations into the phanerogamic flora of Australia more and more, given considerable attention to all signs of cryptogamic plants, &amp; shall, if providence grants me life &amp; health, continue to follow up the study.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will be so kind to draw up the diagnosis for publication in the (transactions or) proceedings of the L.S.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Linnean Society, London.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and if any of the unique specimens you were so disinterested to return, are desired by you, they will at once be returned. Otherwise they will be a valuable addition to our publ. collection.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust you will allow me to name some noble tree of Eastern Australia after you and figure it in my Fragmenta, when I by this means take the opportunity of bearing public testimony to the aid I receive in the investigation of Australian plants.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>IPNI (accessed 26 April 2020) does not list any genus or species published by Mueller based on the name Berkeley.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I received a few fungi from Dr H. Beckler, whom I sent on a botanical mission to the Clarence River.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I have in the Governors despatchbag sent a few specimens of them to you, indeed one of each species. When closing the letter I find I can press them into an envelope; so they will reach you simultaneously with these lines.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wishing you long life and constant health for the sake of science &amp; your numerous friends, </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, dear and venerable Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your humbly attached </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
